  "format": "Sean Fennessey and Amanda Dobbins review the prequel 'A Quiet Place: Day One,' then Chris Ryan joins to take apart Kevin Costner's self-funded Western 'Horizon: An American Saga - Chapter 1.'",
  "segments": [
    {
      "kind": "review",
      "heading": "‘A Quiet Place: Day One’",
      "note": "the prequel, with Amanda Dobbins",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "A Quiet Place: Day One",
          "year": 2024,
          "note": "Michael Sarnoski (of 'Pig') directs the third film in the franchise, from a story he co-wrote with John Krasinski. Lupita Nyong'o plays a terminally ill hospice patient caught in Manhattan on the day the sound-hunting creatures arrive; Joseph Quinn is the stranger she forges a bond with, plus a cat. Sean calls it a surprise and one of the year's best: a contained, melancholy survival story about dying that he found excruciatingly effective for its first 45 minutes, dinged only by a sentimental late song choice. Her goal is a slice of pizza from Patsy's in Harlem. Djimon Hounsou returns from Part II as the connective tissue to the island."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "review",
      "heading": "‘Horizon: An American Saga — Chapter 1’",
      "note": "Kevin Costner's gamble, with Chris Ryan",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Horizon: An American Saga - Chapter 1",
          "year": 2024,
          "note": "Kevin Costner directs, stars, and sank $38 million of his own money into the first of a planned four-part Western, shot on digital in Utah. Three hours, roughly five storylines (Sienna Miller, Costner, Luke Wilson, plus scalp-hunters and a Chinese-immigrant thread), and Costner doesn't appear until the one-hour mark; Luke Wilson arrives at two. The trio agree it plays like Taylor Sheridan TV (a prologue that ends with a trailer for Chapter 2 rather than an ending) and that it's a curious artifact more than a disaster. Nobody's seen it before, but it's not bad; it's just not really a movie yet. Giovanni Ribisi turns up as the possible landowner."
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
